8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 1314, L.D. 1970, “An Act to Amend the
10 Laws Regarding Consent for HIV Testing and Disclosure of Related Medical Information
11 for Insurance Purposes”
12 Amend the bill in section 1 in §19203-A in the headnote (page 1, line 4 in L.D.) by
13 striking out the following: "informed" and inserting the following: 'informed'
14 Amend the bill by striking out all of section 2 and inserting the following:
15 'Sec. 2. 5 MRSA §19203-A, sub-§1, as amended by PL 2007, c. 93, §1, is further
16 amended to read:
17 1. Individual Patient tested; informed consent. Except as provided in this section
18 and section 19203, subsections 4 and 5, an HIV test must be voluntary and undertaken only
19 with a patient's knowledge and understanding that an HIV test is planned informed consent.
20 A patient must be informed orally or in writing that an HIV test will be performed unless
21 the patient declines. Oral or written information required to be given to a patient under this
22 subsection must include an explanation of what an HIV infection involves and the meaning
23 of positive and negative test results. A patient must be provided the opportunity to ask
24 questions, either orally or in writing. Informed consent is not required for repeated HIV
25 testing by health care providers to monitor the course of established infection.
26 A. If a patient declines an HIV test, the health care provider shall document that
27 decision in the patient's medical record.
28 B. The consent of a minor patient's parent or legal guardian is not required to perform
29 an HIV test on the minor patient under this subsection.
30 C. Oral or written information must be given to a patient and must include an
31 explanation of what an HIV infection involves and the meaning of positive and
32 negative test results. A patient must be provided the opportunity to ask questions,
33 either orally or in writing.
34 D. Results of an HIV test performed pursuant to this subsection must be provided to
35 the health care provider that ordered the HIV test.'
